1. A method for responding to a shopper's inquiry seeking price information on a product in a competitive marketplace, comprising: 
receiving the shopper's inquiry for price information on a product; 
searching for price information of advertised products matching the product for which the price is sought; 
assembling identified price information into a response to the inquiry, wherein the price of at least one product is withheld from the response; 
forwarding the assembled response to the shopper along with a cost for obtaining the previously withheld price information; 
receiving the shopper's agreement to buy the previously withheld price information; and 
forwarding to the shopper the previously withheld price information in exchange for the agreed upon payment of the cost for the price information.

